    public class MORHierarchicalDataProperty
extends MORDataPropertyBase
implements MORDataProperty.Sub<MORHierarchicalDataProperty>, MORDataProperty.Super<MORHierarchicalDataProperty>
    A basic implementation for a data property with sub and super properties.

    This is an example of how use the Semantic.Descriptors for implement a data property that is synchronised w.r.t. its Super and Sub properties.
    Its purpose is only to instanciate the MORAxioms.DataLinks for the respective descriptions, as well as call both interfaces in the readSemantic() and writeSemantic() methods. All its constructions are based on MORDataPropertyBase in order to automatically manage a grounding DataInstance.
    You may want to use this class (see also MORDefinitionDataProperty and MORDomainDataProperty as well as other classes in the it.emarolab.owloop.aMORDescriptor.utility package) as templates to build a specific MORDataProperty descriptor that fits your needs and maximises the OWL synchronisation efficiency for data properties.
